Policy.acknowledgement_statement: The dataset(s) used for the analyses described in this manuscript were obtained from the database of Genotype and Phenotype (dbGaP) found at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gap. Samples and associated phenotype data for the Identification of Genes Predisposing to Pelvic Floor Disorders were provided by Lisa Cannon-Albright, Ph.D. and Peggy Norton, MD.
Policy.ic_specific_access_term: In accord with the NIH GWAS Policy for Data Sharing, and as expressed through the submission of the DAR, Approved Users acknowledge the NIH’s expectation that they will not submit findings using the Identification of Genes Predisposing to Pelvic Floor Disorders dataset(s), or updated versions thereof, for publication or presentation for a period of exclusivity for Contributing Investigators concluding with the Embargo Date identified on the dbGaP or other NIH genomic data repository homepage.

GSR_Access.gsr_mode_label: Unrestricted access (institution did not respond within six months)

ConsentGroup.title: Disease-Specific (Pelvic Floor Disorders, RD)
ConsentGroup.name: DS-PFD-RD
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction:
Use of the data must be related to Pelvic Floor Disorders and related disorders.
Use of dataset limited to investigators studying pelvic floor disorders. These would include pelvic organ prolapse, stress urinary incontinence, and other related disorders. These data will be used only for research purposes related to pelvic floor disorders. They will not be used to determine the individual identity of any person or their relationship to another person or for research on non-disease traits.
